## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Responsibility | Depends on |
|-------|----------------|------------|
| `api/v1/router.py` | Aggregates routers from each feature; mounted in `main.py` with prefix `/api/v1` | feature `routes.py` |
| `api/v1/<feature>/` | Feature routes + schemas | `services` |
| `models/` | ORM table/relationship definitions | `core/database` |
| `repositories/` | Queries and persistence (Postgres, Qdrant) | `models`, `core/` |
| `services/` | Business rules, transactions, orchestration | `repositories`, `agents`, `rag` |
| `agents/` | Prompts, tool calling, agent loop | `core/llm`, `repositories`, `rag` |
| `rag/` | Ingestion, retrieval, and vector search | `rag/embeddings`, `repositories` |
| `core/llm/` | LLM adapters (OpenAI, Anthropic, OllamaвҖҰ) | env vars |
| `rag/embeddings/` | Embedding adapters (may use a different vendor than the LLM) | env vars |
| `core/` | Config, DB, Qdrant | env vars |

## Request flow

```
Client вҶ’ api/ (route + DTO) вҶ’ services/ вҶ’ repositories/ вҶ’ PostgreSQL / Qdrant
                                вҶҳ agents/ вҶ’ core/llm/ (chat)
                                         вҶҳ rag/ вҶ’ embeddings/ + Qdrant
```

## LLM providers

Vendor adapters live in `core/llm/` (chat) and `rag/embeddings/` (vectors).
They implement a common interface вҖ” no prompts, tool calling, or business rules.

| Type | Location |
|------|----------|
| LLM chat | `core/llm/` |
| Embeddings | `rag/embeddings/` |

`get_db` lives in `core/database.py`. Services instantiate repos вҖ” routes only pass the session.

## Design rules

1. Thin routes вҖ” no business logic in `api/`
2. Each feature in its own folder вҖ” `api/v1/<feature>/routes.py` + `schemas.py`
3. `api/v1/router.py` centralizes and registers all features
4. Services instantiate repos in `__init__` вҖ” repos concentrate data access
5. Services must not run queries directly вҖ” always via `repositories/`
6. Transactions in `services/` вҖ” commit/rollback do not belong in routes
7. `models/` only defines ORM schema; queries live in repos
8. Versioned routes вҖ” prefix `/api/v1/` via central router

## Testing

Stack: **pytest**, **pytest-cov**, **httpx** (via `requirements-dev.txt`). Dev deps are not installed in the production Docker image.

| Type | Location | What to test |
|------|----------|--------------|
| Unit | `tests/unit/` | Services and core logic with mocked repos/clients |
| API | `tests/api/` | Routes, status codes, and JSON via `TestClient` |
| Integration (later) | `tests/integration/` | Real Postgres / Qdrant when needed |

Run locally (SQLite in-memory вҖ” no Postgres required):

```bash
cd backend
pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
pytest --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing
```

Use `app.dependency_overrides` in `conftest.py` to swap `get_db` and other FastAPI dependencies. Target: **вүҘ 90% coverage** on `app/`.

## Where to put new code

- New HTTP feature вҶ’ `api/v1/<feature>/routes.py` + register in `api/v1/router.py`
- Feature DTOs вҶ’ `api/v1/<feature>/schemas.py`
- DB table вҶ’ `models/<entity>.py`
- Query/persistence вҶ’ `repositories/<entity>_repository.py`
- Business rule вҶ’ `services/<domain>_service.py`
- LLM adapter (chat) вҶ’ `core/llm/<vendor>.py`
- Embedding adapter вҶ’ `rag/embeddings/<vendor>.py`
- Agent tool вҶ’ `agents/tools/`
- Ingestion/retrieval вҶ’ `rag/`
- Unit test вҶ’ `tests/unit/<layer>/test_<module>.py`
- API test вҶ’ `tests/api/test_<feature>.py`

## Legacy (flat) code migration

| Current | Target |
|---------|--------|
| `app/config.py` | `app/core/config.py` |
| `app/database.py` | `app/core/database.py` |
| `app/qdrant.py` | `app/core/qdrant.py` |
| routes in `main.py` | `app/api/v1/<feature>/routes.py` + `app/api/v1/router.py` |
| `main.py` | bootstrap + `app.include_router(v1_router, prefix="/api/v1")` |
